Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  History of Children's Play
Author:  SUTTON-SMiTH
Vol / Page:  50
Edition:
Quote:  Two other kinds of games that played an important role in the girls' playground, along with the singing games, were chasing and dialogue games. in New Zealand, chasing or tagging [51] games are initiated by the `He' player (called the `it' player elsewhere). Before 1900 there seem to have been fewer `He' games.
Notes:

Date:  0/0/1984
Source:  NZ Yesterdays
Author:  KEiTH & MAiN
Vol / Page:  288
Edition:
Quote:  The first out in almost any game was `He' for the next round. Being `He' was an almost mystical ritual and probably caused more tears than anything else.
